Repo: <https://github.com/thiagotbx123/TSA_CORTEX>

  Para testar:
  1. git clone <https://github.com/thiagotbx123/TSA_CORTEX.git>
  2. cd TSA_CORTEX
  3. npm install && npm run build
  4. cp .env.example .env

We are launching this in 4 phases (ATS sandbox > CRM sandbox > ATS demo/activity plan > CRM demo/activity plan). But thats great if thats all you’ve found so far. That would be right in line with what we’ve already discussed with them :raised_hands::skin-tone-2:

Yeah we known the move endpoint exists, but it timestamps the stage transition at the time the stage is moved from what we could tell. The problem is that if we need to show stage transition speed improving over time we cant do that because those dates are system generated at the time the stage is moved with that endpoint.

So far, this is what I've found out.:
1. No new blockers beyond the P1 you already have (backdating stage transitions)
 2. Actually found that the /move endpoint already exists in their ATS API - just not in public docs. So P1 might already be solved. Worth confirming with them if it supports backdating.
 3. Only gap: creating jobs and applications needs UI (no POST endpoint), but that's normal UI automation work, not a blocker.
